places.name: Bogor Botanical Garden
places.description: Expansive, scenic botanical garden showcasing a wide range of tropical flowers & plants.

places.name: Bogor Palace
places.description: The Bogor Palace is one of six Presidential Palaces of Indonesia, it is located in the city of Bogor, West Java. The palace is noted for its distinctive architectural and historical features, as well as the adjoining botanical gardens.

places.name: Kujang Monument
places.description: Built in 1982, this 25-m. monument is constructed to resemble an ancient West Java weapon.

places.name: Museum of Zoology
places.description: Massive, diverse collection of fossilized & preserved animals, including a blue whale skeleton.

places.name: Lawang Suryakencana
places.description: The Suryakencana area has been a business center since the colonial era built around 1808.
